com.SIMRacingApps.Util

Class State

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.SIMRacingApps.Util.State

  • public class State
extends java.lang.Object
    The State class track any state oriented content. It time stamps each state change with a time you give it, so that you can get the amount of time you were in a particular state. It also keeps track of the previous state, so even after changing the state, you can see the state you were in before the change.
    Since:
    1.0
